Chief Elias Mbam, the Chairman, Revenue Mobili­sation Allocation and Fiscal Commission (RMAFC), has described the late Chief Joe Nwodo as a detribalised Ni­gerian who committed his life to the service of the nation. Mbam, in a tribute to the late political icon who died at 77, described him as a co­lossus and intellectual par excellence. He said that Nwodo, an as­tute politician and lawyer, ex­plored his political sagacity to build bridges of unity among politicians and intellectuals, thereby helping to deepen the political system of his time. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! Mbam, in the tribute made available to the News Agen­cy of Nigeria (NAN) on Sat­urday in Abakaliki, said that Enugu State, Ndigbo and the Nigeria nation have lost ‘rare gem’ whose contributions to building a great Nigeria have remained legendary and un­paralleled. “I learnt with grave sad­ness and deep feeling of mel­ancholy of the demise of our dear brother, Dr Joe Nwodo, especially as each time I re­member him, it is with fond memories of a man of unri­valed wisdom and unparal­leled intellect. Week In Review: Buhari, Osinbajo’s Official Engagements Narrow Gauge Lines Not Inferior To Standard Gauge Lines – Minister “Nwodo was one Nigerian politician whose intelligence was as gigantic as his stat­ure, and who unreservedly utilised this God-given talent in pursuit of a peaceful and united Nigeria. “His vast knowledge of constitutional law was evident in his works and speeches and was deployed in his struggle for a Nigeria where everyone, irrespective of religion, tribe and status were equal before the law and equal beneficiaries of the en­tity that is Nigeria.